# Docker Deployment Rules
- Maintain separate development and production Compose files.
- In production, expose only Nginx publicly; keep PostgreSQL, Redis, MinIO, and app services internal.
- Use Nginx as reverse proxy for web, admin, courier, API, and public storage routes.
- MinIO public object access may be exposed through a storage domain; the MinIO console must not be public.
- Protect PostgreSQL and Redis with credentials and no direct public ports in production.
- Target Ubuntu 24.04 LTS and preserve healthchecks, restart policies, backups, and SSL renewal.
- Never commit real secrets or production environment files.
